>
  <p>
    Chagrin Electronic Recycling ("CER," "we," "us," or "our") respects your privacy.
    This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect when you visit
    <strong>fallsrecycle.com</strong> (the "Site") or contact us, how we use that
    information, and the choices you have. By using the Site, you agree to the practices
    described here.
  </p>

  <h2>Information We Collect</h2>

  <h3>Information you give us</h3>
  <p>
    When you fill out our contact form, request a pickup, or email or call us, we collect
    the information you choose to provide. This typically includes your name, email address,
    phone number, and the contents of your message. We only ask for what we need to respond
    to you and provide our services.
  </p>

  <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
  <p>
    Like most websites, our hosting and infrastructure providers may automatically log
    basic technical information when you visit the Site, such as your IP address, browser
    type, device type, referring pages, and the dates and times of your visits. This
    information is used to keep the Site secure, reliable, and working properly.
  </p>

  <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To respond to your questions, messages, and service requests.</li>
    <li>To schedule and provide electronics drop-off and pickup services.</li>
    <li>To operate, maintain, secure, and improve the Site.</li>
    <li>To comply with applicable laws and protect our legal rights.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We do <strong>not</strong> sell or rent your personal information to third parties, and
    we do not use your information for unrelated marketing without your consent.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>
    We use a small number of trusted third-party services to run the Site. These providers
    may process limited information on our behalf, subject to their own privacy policies:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Netlify</strong> — website hosting and contact form processing. Information
      you submit through our contact form is delivered to us through Netlify.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Google Maps</strong> — the embedded map showing our location is provided by
      Google and may collect data as described in Google's privacy policy.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Instagram</strong> — if a social media feed is embedded, content is served by
      Instagram/Meta and is subject to their privacy practices.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third parties. We encourage
    you to review their policies.
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    The Site uses minimal cookies and similar technologies, primarily where required for
    core functionality and for embedded third-party content (such as maps or social feeds).
    You can control or disable cookies through your browser settings. Disabling cookies may
    affect how some features of the Site work.
  </p>

  <h2>How We Protect Your Information</h2>
  <p>
    We take reasonable administrative and technical measures to protect the information we
    collect. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is
    completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Retention</h2>
  <p>
    We keep the information you provide only as long as needed to respond to you, provide
    our services, and meet our legal and recordkeeping obligations. When information is no
    longer needed, we take reasonable steps to delete or de-identify it.
  </p>

  <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    The Site is intended for a general audience and is not directed to children under 13.
    We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe
    a child has provided us information, please contact us and we will delete it.
  </p>

  <h2>Your Choices and Rights</h2>
  <p>
    You may contact us at any time to ask what information we hold about you, to request a
    correction, or to ask us to delete it, subject to any legal obligations we have to
    retain it. To opt out of further communications, simply let us know.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the
    "Last updated" date at the top of this page. Your continued use of the Site after changes
    are posted means you accept the updated policy.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact Us</h2>
  <p>
    If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or how we handle your information,
    contact us at:
